wikipedia_page.main: George Durant Kemp-Welch (4 August 1907 – 18 June 1944) was an English cricketer who played first-class cricket for Warwickshire, Cambridge University, the Marylebone Cricket Club (MCC) and other amateur teams between 1927 and 1936. He was born in Chelsea, London, and died in the V1 bombing of the Guards Chapel, Wellington Barracks, in Westminster.

response: *George Kemp-Welch (1907–1944), English cricketer who played 114 first-class matches
